<subSubSection lastPageId="16" lastPageNumber="17" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1436,1731,2037]" lastBlockId="16.[151,1437,152,298]" lastPageId="16" lastPageNumber="17" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,312,1891,1917]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Remarks</emphasis>
: 
<taxonomicName box="[327,538,1891,1916]" class="Malacostraca" family="Ampeliscidae" genus="Ampelisca" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minuta" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[327,538,1891,1916]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Ampelisca minuta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[544,637,1891,1917]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[544,637,1891,1917]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Mills, 1967" authorityName="Mills" authorityYear="1967" box="[788,1092,1891,1917]" class="Malacostraca" family="Ampeliscidae" genus="Ampelisca" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="declivitatis">
<emphasis box="[788,949,1891,1916]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">A. declivitatis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Mills" box="[955,1092,1891,1917]" pageId="15" pageNumber="24" refString="Mills, E. L. (1967) A reexamination of some species of Ampelisca (Crustacea: Amphipoda) from the east coast of North America. Canadian Journal of Zoology, 45, 635 - 652." type="journal article" year="1967">
Mills, 
<number box="[1031,1092,1891,1917]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="1967.0">1967</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, a small blind ampeliscid, for presenting antenna 
<number box="[379,393,1931,1957]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="1.0">1</number>
of same length that the antenna 
<number box="[775,790,1931,1957]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="2.0">2</number>
peduncle; pereopod 
<number box="[1036,1050,1931,1957]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="7.0">7</number>
merus with a small anterior projection, propodus and dactylus of same length; uropod 
<number box="[798,813,1971,1997]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="3.0">3</number>
with rami lanceolate, beyond absence of eyes. However, 
<taxonomicName box="[216,428,2011,2036]" class="Malacostraca" family="Ampeliscidae" genus="Ampelisca" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minuta" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[216,428,2011,2036]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Ampelisca minuta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[436,531,2011,2037]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[436,531,2011,2037]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
can be differentiated from 
<taxonomicName box="[855,1018,2011,2036]" class="Malacostraca" family="Ampeliscidae" genus="Ampelisca" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="declivitatis">
<emphasis box="[855,1018,2011,2036]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">A. declivitatis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for the anterior margin of the head truncated and ventral margin not oblique, whereas in 
<taxonomicName box="[785,947,152,177]" class="Malacostraca" family="Ampeliscidae" genus="Ampelisca" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="declivitatis">
<emphasis box="[785,947,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">A. declivitatis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the ventral margin is clearly oblique; for the dorsal carina of urosome 
<number box="[502,516,192,218]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="1.0">1</number>
not projected (in 
<taxonomicName box="[732,896,192,217]" class="Malacostraca" family="Ampeliscidae" genus="Ampelisca" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="declivitatis">
<emphasis box="[732,896,192,217]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">A. declivitatis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
urosome 
<number box="[1015,1030,192,218]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="1.0">1</number>
presents an anterior acute projection); pereopod 
<number box="[342,357,232,258]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="7.0">7</number>
basis with posterodistal margin oblique and not transverse as 
<taxonomicName box="[1104,1268,232,257]" class="Malacostraca" family="Ampeliscidae" genus="Ampelisca" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="declivitatis">
<emphasis box="[1104,1268,232,257]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">A. declivitatis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
